# Cloudflare _headers — OpenDeck deck runtime (origin B, decks.open-deck.org).
#
# B is FRAMED by the shell (A): the hidden control bridge and every deck render
# are iframes inside app.open-deck.org. So B must NOT carry a blanket
# `X-Frame-Options: DENY` (that would block the shell from embedding it).
# Framing is instead restricted with CSP `frame-ancestors` to the shell only.
#
# Note: actual deck content at /__deck__/<id>/… is emitted by THIS origin's
# service worker (www-deck/sw.js), which sets its own per-response CSP — these
# header rules govern only the static bridge + SW script that Cloudflare serves.

/*
  X-Content-Type-Options: nosniff
  Referrer-Policy: strict-origin-when-cross-origin

# The control bridge: only the shell may frame it. Its bootstrap script is
# inline, hence 'unsafe-inline' on script-src.
/bridge.html
  Content-Security-Policy: default-src 'self'; script-src 'self' 'unsafe-inline'; base-uri 'none'; form-action 'none'; frame-ancestors https://app.open-deck.org
  Cache-Control: no-cache

# The deck service worker must update promptly.
/sw.js
  Cache-Control: no-cache
